messages.content: What is the purpose of TW-CUI-Util?
TW-CUI-Util contains multiple utility nodes that improve ease-of-use and combine various nodes into single ones to streamline workflows.
Are there a list of the included nodes in this repository?
Yes, you can refer to the project's [**wiki**](https://github.com/TW-CUI/TW-CUI-Util/wiki) for a detailed list of included nodes.
What is the licensing information of TW-CUI-Util?
TW-CUI-Util is licensed under GPL-3.0 unless otherwise specified.
How can I contribute to the TW-CUI-Util project?
Consult the project's [**wiki**](https://github.com/TW-CUI/TW-CUI-Util/wiki) for details on contribution guidelines.
What platforms or environments does TW-CUI-Util support?
The documentation does not specify the supported platforms or environments.
Can TW-CUI-Util nodes be used with other custom nodes?
Yes, TW-CUI-Util nodes can be combined with other custom nodes in workflows as described in the usage information on the [**wiki**](https://github.com/TW-CUI/TW-CUI-Util/wiki).
Is there a testing framework used in TW-CUI-Util to ensure code quality?
Yes, the repository includes a code coverage report, but the specific testing framework used is not mentioned.
